export namespace IOpenAiSchema {
  /**
   * Unknown type schema info.
   *
   * It means the type of the value is `any`.
   */
  export interface IUnknown extends __IAttribute {
    /**
     * Type is never be defined.
     */
    type?: undefined;
  }
}
In the LLM function calling schema, unknown type is expressed as above.Within framework of the TypeScript definition, it is equivalent any and unknown types.Of course, as the type is literally unknown, LLM cannot compose proper value for the type. Therefore, it would better to avoid to using the unknown (any) type when you are considering an API to be utilized by the LLM function calling.

